SIMPLE: swig
RECORDS: 3

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Swig
<hw>Swig</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <ety>[Cf. D.
<ets>zwelgen</ets> to swallow, E. <ets>swallow</ets>, v.t.]</ety>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>To drink in long draughts; to gulp; <as>as, to
<ex>swig</ex> cider</as>.</def> <mark>[Colloq.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To suck.</def> <mark>[Obs. or Archaic]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The lambkins <qex>swig</qex> the teat.</q>
<rj><qau>Creech.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Swig</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Swig
<hw>Swig</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A long draught.</def>
<mark>[Colloq.]</mark> <rj><au>Marryat.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Naut.)</fld> <def>A tackle with ropes which are not
parallel.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>A beverage consisting of warm beer flavored with
spices, lemon, etc.</def> <mark>[Prov. Eng.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Swig</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 3 ====
HEADWORD: Swig
<hw>Swig</hw>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <ety>[Cf. Prov. E. <ets>swig</ets> to
leak out, AS. <ets>sw⟦imac⟧jian</ets> to be silent,
<ets>sw⟦imac⟧can</ets> to evade, escape.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>To
castrate, as a ram, by binding the testicles tightly with a string, so
that they mortify and slough off.</def> <mark>[Prov. Eng.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Naut.)</fld> <def>To pull upon (a tackle) by
throwing the weight of the body upon the fall between the block and a
cleat.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Swill</ent>⟦br⟧
